nd-school/school/profile?school=1982 |website=educationcounts.govt.nz |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (New Zealand)|Ministry of Education]]}}</ref> with a roll of {{NZ school roll data|1982|y}},<ref name=\"ero1982\">{{cite web |title=Tarrangower School Education Review Office Report |url=http://www.ero.govt.nz/report-view?id=1982 |website=ero.govt.nz |publisher=[[Education Review Office]]}}</ref> and Turaki School,<ref name=\"official2040\">{{cite web |title=Turaki School Official School Website |url=http://www.turakiprimary.school.nz |website=turakiprimary.school.nz}}</ref><ref name=\"moe2040\">{{cite web |title=Turaki School Ministry of Education School Profile |url=https://www.educationcounts.govt.nz/find-school/school/profile?school=2040 |website=educationcounts.govt.nz |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (New Zealand)|Ministry of Education]]}}</ref> with a roll of {{NZ school roll data|2040|y}}.<ref name=\"ero2040\">{{cite web |title=Turaki School Education Review Office Report |url=http://www.ero.govt.nz/report-view?id=2040 |website=ero.govt.nz |publisher=[[Education Review Office]]}}</ref>\n\nSt Patrick's Catholic School is a co-educational state-integrated Catholic primary school for Year 1 to 8 students,<ref name=\"moe1961\">{{cite web |title=Ministry of Education School Profile |url=https://www.educationcounts.govt.nz/find-school/school/profile?school=1961 |website=educationcounts.govt.nz |publisher=[[Ministry of Education (New Zealand)|Ministry of Education]]}}</ref> with a roll of {{NZ school roll data|1961|y}}.<ref name=\"ero1961\">{{cite web |title=Education Review Office Report |url=http://www.ero.govt.nz/report-view?id=1961 |website=ero.govt.nz |publisher=[[Education Review Office]]}}</ref>\n\n== Notable people==\n* T.J. Meredith \u2013  great-grandson of [[Theodore of Corsica]], joined [[Royal Navy]] age 14, [[CSS Louisiana]] in 1862 [[American Civil War]], under [[Duncan Alexander Cameron|General Cameron]] [[New Zealand Wars]], [[Waikato Mounted Rifles]] [[World War I]], before coming the proprietor of Taumarunui's Meredith House with wife Margaret Lovett.<ref>[[#Craig1990|Craig 1990]], T.J. Meredith p.147</ref>\n\n===Students of Taumarunui High School===\n* Prof. James L. Beck<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.its.caltech.edu/~jimbeck/ |title=James L. Beck |publisher=Its.caltech.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-10-23}}</ref> \u2013 Professor of Engineering and Applied Science, [[California Institute of Technology]].\n* Prof. [[John C. Butcher]] {{post-nominals|country=NZL|ONZM}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.math.auckland.ac.nz/~butcher/ |title=John Butcher's Homepage |publisher=Math.auckland.ac.nz |accessdate=2013-10-23}}</ref> \u2013 Honorary Research Professor, Dept. of Mathematics, [[University of Auckland]].\n* [[Ben Fouhy]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.benfouhy.com|title=Ben Fouhy : Words|publisher=Benfouhy.com|accessdate=2013-10-23}}</ref> world champion kayaker.\n* [[Marc Hunter|Marc]] and [[Todd Hunter]] from the band [[Dragon (band)|Dragon]].\n* [[Ivan Mercep]], 2008 recipient of the [[New Zealand Institute of Architects]] Gold Medal.\n* [[Jenny Ludlam]] \u2013  actress.\n\n===Born in Taumarunui===\n[[File:Carmen Rupe.jpg|thumb|150px|[[Carmen Rupe]]]]\n* 1914 \u2013 [[Wiremu Te Awhitu|Wiremu Hakopa Toa Te Awhitu SM]] (1914\u20131994) was the first M\u0101ori to be ordained a [[Catholic]] priest.\n* 1935 \u2013 [[Don Selwyn]], Actor, Director, Stage and Screen, [[Ng\u0101ti Kuri]] and [[Te Aup\u014duri]] (1935\u20132007) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thearts.co.nz/artist_page.php&aid=5&type=bio |title=The Arts Foundation : Don Selwyn \u2013 Biography |publisher=Thearts.co.nz |date= |accessdate=2015-01-18}}</ref>\n* 1936 \u2013 [[Carmen Rupe]] (n\u00e9 Trevor Rupe, 1935\u201315 December 2011) \u2013 [[Wellington]] personality (mayoral candidate (1977), drag queen, cafe owner and brothel keeper).<ref>{{cite news |first=Shabnam |last=Dastgheib |title=Birthday girl Carmen hits town |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/2946328/Birthday-girl-Carmen-hits-town/ |work=[[The Dominion Post (Wellington)|The Dominion Post]] |date=9 October 2009 |accessdate=16 December 2011}}</ref>{{sfn|O'Keefe and Fox|2008|p=249}}<ref>{{cite news |title=Colourful Wellington identity Carmen dies |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/dominion-post/news/6142914/Colourful-Wellington-identity-Carmen-dies |work=[[The Dominion Post (Wellington)|The Dominion Post]] |date=15 December 2011 |accessdate=15 December 2011}}</ref>\n* 1939 \u2013 [[David Penny]], theoretical biologist.<ref name=\"massey1\">{{cite web|title=Professor Emeritus joins prominent US Academy|url=http://www.massey.ac.nz/massey/about-massey/news/article.cfm?mnarticle_uuid=FB8FD7F2-72A8-4181-A614-B9CD5D999D92|publisher=Massey University|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref>\n* 1945 \u2013 [[Carole Shepheard]], artist.\n* 1951 \u2013 [[Joe Karam]], rugby union player, researcher and investigator for [[David Bain]]'s legal team.\n* 1952 \u2013 [[Ian Ferguson (canoeist)|Ian Ferguson]], Olympic canoer.\n* 1952 \u2013 [[Max Mariu|Max Takuira Matthew Mariu SM]] (1952\u20132005), Auxiliary Catholic Bishop of Hamilton (1988\u20132005), first [[M\u0101ori people|M\u0101ori]] to be ordained a Catholic bishop.\n* 1953 \u2013 [[Marc Hunter]], lead singer of [[Dragon (band)|Dragon]].\n* 1955 \u2013 [[Mahin\u0101rangi Tocker]], singer. \n* 1956 \u2013 [[Len Brown]] Mayor of Auckland\n* 1958 \u2013 [[Jillian Smith]], field hockey player.\n* 1958 \u2013 [[Lindsay Crocker]], cricketer.\n* 1960s [[Timothy J. Sinclair]], political scientist.\n* 1971 \u2013 [[Kyle Chapman]], former leader of the [[New Zealand National Front]]\n* 1973 \u2013 [[Chris McCormack (triathlete)|Chris McCormack]] World Champion Ironman Triathlete (2007, 2010).\n\n=== Resident and New Years Honours recipients===\n[[File:PeiTeHurinuiJones1930.jpg|thumb|150px|[[Pei Te Hurinui Jones]]]]\n* [[1956 New Year Honours|1956]] \u2013 [[Order of the British Empire#Officer of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|OBE]] \u2013 Pateriki Joseph Hura \u2013 For services to the M\u0101ori people, especially as a member of the Board of Maori Affairs.\n* [[1957 New Year Honours|1957]] \u2013 [[Order of the British Empire#Member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|MBE]] \u2013 Mrs Catherine Goodsir \u2013 For social welfare services\n* [[1958 New Year Honours|1958]] \u2013 MBE \u2013 [[Rumatiki Ruth Wright|Mrs Rumatiki Wright]] of Raetihi. For services to the M\u0101ori people, especially as Senior Lady M\u0101ori Welfare Officer\n* [[1961 New Year Honours|1961]] \u2013 OBE \u2013 [[Pei Te Hurinui Jones]] \u2013 For services to the M\u0101ori people.\n* [[1967 New Year Honours|1967]] \u2013 MBE \u2013 James Dempsey [[Justice of the peace#New Zealand|J.P.]] \u2013  chairman of the Taumarunui [[Counties of New Zealand|County Council]].\n* [[1970 New Year Honours|1970]] \u2013 [[British Empire Medal|BEM]] \u2013 Eric Raymond Clark \u2013 For services to the community and interest in the education of the M\u0101ori people.\n* [[1974 New Year Honours|1974]] \u2013 BEM \u2013 Arthur Tukiri Anderson \u2013 For services to the Returned Services Association and the community\n* [[1979 New Year Honours|1979]] \u2013 [[Order of the British Empire#Knight Commander or Dame Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|KBE]] \u2013 [[Hepi Te Heuheu|Hepi Hoani Te Heuheu]] \u2013 For services to the M\u0101ori people and community.\n* [[1995 New Year Honours|1995]] \u2013 [[Order of the British Empire#Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire|CBE]] \u2013 Alexander Phillips QSM \u2013 For services to the M\u0101ori people.\n* [[1998 New Year Honours|1998]] \u2013 [[New Zealand Order of Merit#Member|MNZM]] \u2013 John Stacey Black J.P. \u2013 For services to the community.\n* [[2000 New Year Honours|2000]] \u2013 [[Queen's Service Medal|QSM]] \u2013 Jean Bassett \u2013 For Community Service\n* [[2001 New Year Honours|2001]] \u2013 QSM \u2013 Mrs Verna Lenice Warner J.P. \u2013 For Community Service\n* [[2002 New Year Honours|2002]] \u2013 MNZM \u2013 Mrs Nansi Whetu Dewes \u2013 For services to M\u0101ori and the community\n* [[2002 New Year Honours|2002]] \u2013 QSM \u2013 Barry David FISHER, of Taumarunui. Chief Fire Officer, Taumarunui Volunteer Fire Brigade, New Zealand Fire Service \u2013 For Services to the community\n* [[2003 New Year Honours|2003]] \u2013 QSM \u2013 Leonard Patrick Harwood \u2013 For Public Services\n* [[2007 New Year Honours|2007]] \u2013 QSM \u2013 Mr William Vernon McMinn \u2013 For services to music.\n* [[2009 New Year Honours|2009]] \u2013 MNZM \u2013 Ngarau Tarawa \u2013  For services to M\u0101ori and community education\n* [[2010 New Year Honours|2010]] \u2013 QSM \u2013 Mrs Lorraine Ivy Edwards J.P. \u2013 For services to the community.\n* [[2012 New Year Honours|2012]] \u2013 MNZM \u2013 Ian Trevor Corney \u2013 For services to agriculture\n* [[2013 New Year Honours|2013]] \u2013 [[New Zealand Order of Merit#Officer|ONZM]] \u2013 Susan May Morris \u2013 For services to local government.\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==References==\n*{{cite book |last=Craig |first=Dick |title=The King Country |year=1990 |publisher=Waitomo News |location=Waitomo |ref=Craig1990}}\n*{{cite book |last1=O'Keefe | first1=Tracie | first2=Katrina | last2=Fox | title=[[Trans People in Love]] | publisher=Routledge |date=6 June 2008 |chapter=Chapter 24: Madam Carmen \u2013 Carmen Rupe |isbn=978-0-7890-3572-1 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/?id=AigQSatPMgAC |ref = {{sfnRef|O'Keefe and Fox|2008|p=249}}}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Taumarunui}}\n* [https://www.taumarunui.co.nz Taumarunui website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050408235349/http://www.ruapehutourism.co.nz/TAUMARUNUI_HISTORY.htm Local History]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070630215030/http://www.taumarunuihigh.school.nz/ Taumarunui High School]\n* [http://www.riverboats.homestead.com/RiverboatLan